Here's a description of what's visible in the screenshot:

The screen shows p5.js, an online Javascript coding environment (likely the web editor at editor.p5js.org). The filename is "sketch.js".  The code editor displays Javascript code that initializes an array `arr` containing strings "zeroth", "100", "banana", and "yoghurt". The canvas preview area displays the text "zeroth", "100", "banana", and "yoghurt" stacked vertically in white text on a dark background. The code appears to be iterating through the array and displaying each element with some offset positioning.

```javascript
// if an array is a list of elements...
let arr = ["zeroth", 100, "banana", "yoghurt"];
arrays are 'zero indexed' <- that means that we count from 0.

function setup() {
  createCanvas(400, 400);
  textSize(16);
}

function draw() {
  background(20);
  fill(200, 0, 0);

  // for loop
  for(let y = 0; y < arr.length; y++) {
    text(arr[y], 50, 70 + y * 100);
  }

  fill(255)
  //for-in loop
  for (let el in arr) {
    text(arr[el], 55, 70 + el * 100)
  }
}
```

